<table class="infobox biography vcard" style="width:22em">
 <tr>
  <th colspan="2" style="text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold">
   <span class="fn">
    Leon "Pee Wee" Whittaker
   </span>
  </th>
 </tr>
 <tr>
  <th colspan="2" style="text-align:center">
   Notes
  </th>
 </tr>
 <tr>
  <td colspan="2" style="text-align:center">
   <div style="text-align: left;">
    <p>
     (1) Whittaker appeared to have inherited his musical talent from the maternal side of his family, with his mother and grandfather being adept musicians.
    </p>
    <p>
     (2) Born in
     <a href="/wiki/Newellton,_Louisiana" title="Newellton, Louisiana">
      Newellton
     </a>
     in northeastern
     <a href="/wiki/Louisiana" title="Louisiana">
      Louisiana
     </a>
     , Whittaker lived in several
     <a href="/wiki/Mississippi_River" title="Mississippi River">
      Mississippi River
     </a>
     cities during his long career, having spent his last four
     <a href="/wiki/Decade" title="Decade">
      decades
     </a>
     in
     <a href="/wiki/Ferriday,_Louisiana" title="Ferriday, Louisiana">
      Ferriday
     </a>
     in
     <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Concordia_Parish" title="Concordia Parish">
      Concordia Parish
     </a>
     .
    </p>
    <p>
     (3) Whittaker specialized in
     <a href="/wiki/Rhythm_and_blues" title="Rhythm and blues">
      rhythm and blues
     </a>
     ,
     <a href="/wiki/Jazz" title="Jazz">
      jazz
     </a>
     and
     <a href="/wiki/Rock_and_roll" title="Rock and roll">
      rock and roll
     </a>
     <a href="/wiki/Music" title="Music">
      music
     </a>
     .
    </p>
    (4) Before his death, Whittaker donated a
    <a href="/wiki/Trombone" title="Trombone">
     trombone
    </a>
    to the
    <a href="/wiki/Delta_Music_Museum" title="Delta Music Museum">
     Delta Music Museum
    </a>
    in Ferriday.
   </div>
  </td>
 </tr>
</table>
